<sec id="summary">
  <title>Summary</title>
  <p>This package implements efficient, high-quality sample rate
  conversion using the band-limited sinc interpolation method
  (<xref alt="Smith, 2002" rid="ref-RESAMPLE" ref-type="bibr">Smith,
  2002</xref>). This method supports fast sample rate conversion for
  long and multi-channel signals. Its functionality and features are
  similar to <monospace>libsamplerate</monospace>
  (<xref alt="Castro, 2005" rid="ref-libsamplerate" ref-type="bibr">Castro,
  2005</xref>), but it differs by having a permissive (BSD-style)
  license, and it is written in Cython so that it is easier to install
  and use within larger Python projects.</p>
</sec>
